= More Religion?</span><hr size=1> &quot;I don't believe there is a god so I don't need an &quot;excuse&quot; to turn away from him. If I believed there was a god, turning away from him would be the last thing I would be looking for an excuse to do. If I could believe in all that eternal life/bliss/etc. why wouldn't I want it?&quot;<br>
<br>
ITA with this - why is it so hard to understand that some people just don't believe in any gods?? We aren't turning away from any gods, because we don't believe any exist...that is like saying that every time you walk through your front door, you are turning your back on the pink dragon inside your house - it just doesn't work.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why does there have to be an bad experience for me not to believe in god. I can always remember not believing. It has nothing to do with my experience with religion. That is such a copout to say that we must be damaged in some way not to believe. We just don’t plain and simple.&quot;<br>
<br>
ITA with this also - I've not had any bad experiences with religion - I've *never* believed in a god, for as long as I can remember.  The whole idea just makes no sense to me at all - I truely cannot fathom how people can believe in a god...simple as that. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.growthspurts.com/drivee/images/434360233606.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonbon2d>bonbon2D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Apologist in Training</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/23/03 3:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=126.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.iambornagainru.org/bab/Avatars/cm09.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bad Times = More Religion?</span><hr size=1> ...And the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>important</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> word in my statement would be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>some</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, that is, not everyone...therefore pretty sure that wouldn't apply to you DL or anyone else who makes the same claims as you.  <br>
