What I was saying was that many like to use the old, tired excuse of &quot;Why would I want to believe in a God who is supposed to be all-loving, yet allows this to happen?&quot;  Those are the ones who are using it as an excuse.<br>
<br>
If you've chosen not to believe out of your own knowledge instead of allowing an excuse like tragedy in our lives to be a cop-out for religion, then at least you've gone about it in a way that I can respect!<br>
