ITA with Candy here. We often lament that theists assume we are atheists due to some trajedy or negative experience with religion or a priest, when this is rarely the case--hard to turn around and use negative experiences as an excuse to not believe then. The problem with most modern western folks is that we think any god is automatically good and loving when even a cursory reading of even the OT should wipe that notion right out of our heads!! <br>
<br>
On the subject of reaction to tragedy I have to say I think it usually drives religious people deeper into their faith. Isn't that one of the main features of faith is for explanations of the unfathomable and the numbing effect? (Okay crowd control too, but that's more for those holding power than the masses themselves). Gosh, take tragedy and suffering away and there's really not much left to believe in anymore&gt;D<br>
