<br>
It takes a lot of self control to allow your kids to make mistakes and learn from them, when you could just reach out and stop the pain. Its that indepedence thing, you were talking about.  At some point in time parents have to let go and let their kids live  and learn from  their own choices and the consequences.  His giving us our agency does not mean that he is any less Omnipotent.   - Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doublelatte>Double Latte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Got Milk?</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/24/03 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=126.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: control</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>He does not excercise control over our choices.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
