DL <p>&quot;Beware of a clear and present evil in the name of some future, nebulous good.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luvthatdyl>LuvThatDyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/24/03 5:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=126.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: control</span><hr size=1> If anyone here would sit by and watch children suffer when you had the omnipotent powers to stop it, then raise your hand.  <br>
<br>
I don't use tragedies as the reason for questioning God's existence, but they are definitely a factor.  I used to be more of a believer in God eventhough I always had my skepticism and issues with organized religion.  When I had my miscarriage I really thought God was punishing me.  If anything, I had more faith during that time because I of how strongly I believed this.  Then again, I wasn't really myself when that happened, and I know now that I was being irrational, especially since I've never done anything in my life that warrants the pain of losing a child.  Unlike this so called God, I've never taken the life of someone else's child.  When it comes to my recent tragedy, nothing has changed for me when it comes to beliefs.  I came to the conclusion that I was agnostic well before this happened, and I still hold to that.  I actually find more comfort in knowing that this wasn't part of anyone's conscious effort.  It just happened.  It wasn't done to test our faith, and it wasn't done to punish any of us.  I have not waivered despite all of this.  I know that other people do.  Some people take on a stronger belief because they can't grasp that things in life just happen for no good reason.  Some people totally lose faith at that point because they are pissed that God wasn't their servant who would look out for every aspect of their particular life while ignoring those starving children in Africa.  These are the range of emotions people go through, and since God is an integral part of their life, then that is who they take their frustrations out on.  I choose to just deal with what happened instead of using some deity as my punching bag.  I don't believe this accident happened because I've taken the agnostic route.  Why punish my sister for this?  Why punish her passenger who is still in a coma?  They weren't martyrs for other people to look at their faith.  I also don't think they were martyrs for us to learn some lesson.  My miscarriage did teach me that a healthy baby isn't something to take for granted, but I don't think that child's life was taken just for me to learn this.  I think I just had the strength within me to stand up and see what I can learn from this on my own.  Life gave me a lemon, and I chose to make lemonade.  I don't think it is devine lemonade, I think it is just a strength I found in myself.  Now that my sister is gone, I'm trying to do the same thing.  God didn't take my sister or my baby in order to get me to appreciate the people in my lives, I just decided to make the best out of a bad situation instead of sitting around whining about my bad luck and yelling at the sky.  I'm not going to turn to a deity like a bottle of anti-depressants and look for a quick fix.  <br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=126.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=126.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=126.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=126.topic&index=27><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.threadControl?topicID=126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form acti